com.ibm.team.interop.common

Interface ISyncRule

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAuditable, IAuditableHandle, IItem, IItemHandle, IManagedItem, IManagedItemHandle, ISyncRuleHandle

    public interface ISyncRule
extends ISyncRuleHandle, IAuditable
    A synchronization rule defines how external object properties and Jazz item properties are transformed into each other. If an external object is being synchronized with a Jazz item (as opposed to just having some of its state replicated in the Jazz repository), the sync rule defines the association between external properties and Jazz properties, and the names of both Jazz and external "object managers" that know how to read and write the objects being synchronized.
    Since:
    0.5

      • getSyncItemTypeQualifier

        java.lang.String getSyncItemTypeQualifier()
        Get any further qualification of the item type that this synchronization rule applies to, if any. An item manager can distinguish between different "sub-types" of an item type by defining some sort of qualifier for an item (e.g. the value of a certain property). If this value is null or empty, then the synchronization rule applies to all items of the type identified by getSyncItemType().
        Returns:

      • isSyncAllItemStates

        boolean isSyncAllItemStates()
        Determine whether all item states should be synchronized out to an external object. If false, only the current state of an item is considered when changes are detected for outgoing synchronization. If true, and the item maintains history, then all states created since the last time the item was synchronized out (all existing state the first time it is synchronized) are "replayed" to the external object.

        The default value for this property is false.

        Returns:
        true if all states of an item with history should be synchronized out to an external object, false if only the current state should be synchronized out

      • setSyncAllItemStates

        void setSyncAllItemStates(boolean syncAll)
        Set whether all item states of an item with history should be synchronized out to an external object.
        Parameters:
        syncAll - true to synchronize all item state out to an external object, false to synchronize only the current state
        See Also:
        isSyncAllItemStates()

      • addCandidatePropertyMappings

        IPropertyMapping[] addCandidatePropertyMappings(ITypeInfoDTO itemTypeInfo,
                                              ITypeInfoDTO externalTypeInfo,
                                              boolean mappedOnly)
        Add mappings for the properties of item and/or external types. If both item type and external type information is provided, then similarly-named properties will be mapped to each other. In this case, if the mappedOnly argument is true, only properties that could be mapped are added, otherwise all item properties are added, whether they could be mapped or not. If no item type info is supplied, then all external properties are added.
        Parameters:
        itemTypeInfo - information about the item type's properties, or null if item type info not known
        externalTypeInfo - information about the external type's properties; must not be null
        mappedOnly - if itemTypeInfo is not null, then true means to add only item properties that could be mapped to external properties, and false means to add all item properties
        Returns:
        the new mappings that were added; never null; may be empty
        Since:
        0.7

      • addCandidateValueMappings

        IValueMapping[] addCandidateValueMappings(IPropertyMapping propertyMapping,
                                        IPropertyInfoDTO itemPropertyInfo,
                                        IPropertyInfoDTO externalPropertyInfo,
                                        boolean mappedOnly)
        Add mappings for the possible values of an item and/or external property. If both item and external property information is provided, then similarly-named values will be mapped to each other. In this case, if the mappedOnly argument is true, only values that could be mapped are added, otherwise all item values are added, whether they could be mapped or not. If no item property info is supplied, then all external values are added.
        Parameters:
        propertyMapping - the property mappings to add value mappings to
        itemPropertyInfo - information about the allowed property values, or null if item property info not known
        externalPropertyInfo - information about the external property values; must not be null
        mappedOnly - if itemPropertyInfo is not null, then true means to add only item properties that could be mapped to external properties, and false means to add all item properties
        Returns:
        the new mappings that were added; never null; may be empty
        Since:
        0.7

      • getMaxCycleCount

        int getMaxCycleCount()
        Get the cycle count limit for this synchronization rule. The limit is the number of incoming/outgoing synchronization cycles that will cause the proxy status to be set to IExternalProxy#STATUS_CYCLE, so it is one greater than the number of permitted cycles. The default value is 0, which allows 1 cycle.
        Returns:
        the cycle limit count

        Parameters:
        value - the new cycle count limit; must be non-negative

      • setProjectArea

        void setProjectArea(IProjectAreaHandle projectAreaHandle)

        Parameters:

      • getEnabledTeamAreas

        java.util.List<ITeamAreaHandle> getEnabledTeamAreas()
        Get any team areas that have been explicitly enabled for outgoing synchronization of unconnected artifacts. If there are no explicitly enabled team areas, all team areas in the project area associated with this synchronization rule are considered to be enabled.

        This affects whether external connections are attempted for artifacts that currently have no external connection. When an unconnected artifact is created or modified, and there is a synchronization rule that applies to the artifact in the project area associated with the artifact, then if the synchronization rule has any explicitly enabled team areas, the artifact must also be associated with one of the team areas in order to be considered for connection to an external object.

        To modify the list of explicitly enabled team areas, use this method to retrieve the list, then operate on the list directly.

        Returns:
        any team areas explicitly enabled for outgoing synchronization of unconnected artifacts; may be empty; never null
        Since:
        0.6

        Returns:
        any external repository connection info; may be null
        Since:

      • importDefinition

        void importDefinition(java.io.Reader input)
                      throws TeamRepositoryException
        Import an external definition of a synchronization rule into this object. This object must be a new item or a working copy of an existing item. It can be saved after the import.

        The external definition format is XML, with the schema defined in the schema/syncrule.xsd file. Note that a definition need not be complete; most elements are optional. Whatever properties are present in the definition will be applied to this object, so this is really just a way of setting properties.

        Note that if the input is coming from byte-oriented media, since UTF-8 encoding is assumed, the input Reader must be configured to use the UTF-8 character set for decoding bytes into characters.

        Parameters:
        input - a reader for the source of the imported definition
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - if the definition is invalid
        Since:
        0.6

      • exportDefinition

        void exportDefinition(java.io.Writer output)
                      throws TeamRepositoryException
        Export an external definition of this synchronization rule.

        The external definition format is XML, with the schema defined in the schema/syncrule.xsd file.

        Note that if the output is going to byte-oriented media, since UTF-8 encoding is assumed, the output Writer must be configured to use the UTF-8 character set for encoding characters into bytes.

        Parameters:
        output - a writer for the destination of the exported definition
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException - if there is an output error
        Since:
        0.6
